---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Custos — Sovereign AI architecture for SA regulated industries">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section style="max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 5rem 1.5rem 4rem;">
    <p style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--accent); letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; margin: 0 0 1.5rem;">Custos</p>
    <h1 style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem); font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.15; letter-spacing: -0.04em; color: #ffffff; margin: 0 0 1.5rem; max-width: 22ch;">
      Sovereign AI architecture for SA regulated industries.
    </h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.125rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; max-width: 52ch; margin: 0 0 2.5rem;">
      Helping South African medical aid, banking, and insurance enterprises deploy production AI on sovereign infrastructure. POPIA-compliant by design.
    </p>
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap;">
      <a href="/writing" style="background: var(--accent); color: #000; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.875rem; padding: 0.6rem 1.25rem; border-radius: 4px;">
        Read the writing
      </a>
      <a href="/about" style="border: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--text); font-size: 0.875rem; padding: 0.6rem 1.25rem; border-radius: 4px;">
        About Custos
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div style="max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 1.5rem;">
    <hr style="border: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--border);" />
  </div>

  <!-- What we do -->
  <section style="max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 4rem 1.5rem;">
    <h2 style="font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-muted); margin: 0 0 2.5rem;">What Custos does</h2>
    <div style="display: grid; gap: 1.5rem; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));">

      <div style="border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 6px; padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--bg-surface);">
        <p style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--accent); margin: 0 0 0.75rem;">01</p>
        <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #fff; margin: 0 0 0.75rem;">Sovereign AI Readiness Assessment</h3>
        <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.65; margin: 0;">
          A 2 to 3 week engagement. We map your current AI workloads, identify which handle POPIA-sensitive data, and design a sovereign deployment path on Cassava AI Factory, on-prem GPU infrastructure, or hybrid.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div style="border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 6px; padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--bg-surface);">
        <p style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--accent); margin: 0 0 0.75rem;">02</p>
        <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #fff; margin: 0 0 0.75rem;">Architecture Design</h3>
        <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.65; margin: 0;">
          Reference architectures for POPIA-compliant LLM inference, production RAG over regulated corpora, observability stacks, and identity federation for enterprise AI deployments.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div style="border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 6px; padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--bg-surface);">
        <p style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--accent); margin: 0 0 0.75rem;">03</p>
        <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #fff; margin: 0 0 0.75rem;">Production AI Engineering</h3>
        <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.65; margin: 0;">
          Building production LLM pipelines, agentic systems, and prompt-engineering guardrails on the Cassava AI Factory and sovereign infrastructure. Modal, vLLM, Anthropic Claude, Kubernetes.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <div style="max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 1.5rem;">
    <hr style="border: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--border);" />
  </div>

  <!-- Context -->
  <section style="max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 4rem 1.5rem;">
    <h2 style="font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-muted); margin: 0 0 2rem;">The context</h2>
    <div style="display: grid; gap: 1.5rem;">
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; align-items: flex-start;">
        <span style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--accent); min-width: 2rem; padding-top: 0.15rem; flex-shrink: 0;">01</span>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7;">
          <strong style="color: var(--text);">Cassava AI Factory launched in SA in October 2025.</strong> NVIDIA infrastructure, on-shore GPU compute. The first credible sovereign inference option at scale in South Africa.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; align-items: flex-start;">
        <span style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--accent); min-width: 2rem; padding-top: 0.15rem; flex-shrink: 0;">02</span>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7;">
          <strong style="color: var(--text);">POPIA Section 72 restricts cross-border data transfers.</strong> Most default AI cloud deployments route inference through US or EU data centres. For health data, financial data, and biometrics, this creates real architectural and compliance obligations.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; align-items: flex-start;">
        <span style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--accent); min-width: 2rem; padding-top: 0.15rem; flex-shrink: 0;">03</span>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7;">
          <strong style="color: var(--text);">Every SA board is asking where their AI data lives.</strong> Most enterprises don't have a clean answer. Global consultancies charge R10m+ minimums. Custos works in the R75k to R500k range, with SA-specific sovereign infrastructure depth.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div style="max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 1.5rem;">
    <hr style="border: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--border);" />
  </div>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section style="max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="background: var(--bg-surface); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 2.5rem; text-align: center;">
      <h2 style="font-size: 1.375rem; font-weight: 600; color: #fff; letter-spacing: -0.025em; margin: 0 0 0.75rem;">Running research interviews</h2>
      <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; max-width: 48ch; margin: 0 auto 2rem;">
        I'm talking to SA CIOs, CROs, and compliance leads working on AI governance and sovereign infrastructure. 25 minutes. No pitch.
      </p>
      <a
        href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/tristandekock"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
        style="display: inline-block; background: var(--accent); color: #000; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.875rem; padding: 0.7rem 1.5rem; border-radius: 4px;"
      >
        Connect on LinkedIn
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
